00:14:25,860 --> 00:14:28,140
Talking is unique to humans 

214
00:14:28,260 --> 00:14:31,000
An animal might make ten different sounds 

215
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:34,780
But an adult human knows more than twenty thousand words 

216
00:14:34,780 --> 00:14:39,940
Additionally , with the only animal that expresses thoughts in full sentences 

217
00:14:40,110 --> 00:14:43,110
Researchers don't think language was invented 

218
00:14:43,110 --> 00:14:45,670
Instead , they think it's evolved 

219
00:14:45,970 --> 00:14:47,690
How did talking evolve 

220
00:14:47,890 --> 00:14:50,010
There are two main theories 

221
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:55,040
The first theory is that language started with people making different sounds 

222
00:14:55,060 --> 00:14:59,280
Mostly imitating the things around them like animal calls 

223
00:14:59,280 --> 00:15:02,140
Nature sounds , and the sounds of tools 

224
00:15:02,380 --> 00:15:06,060
Perhaps they made the sound of wind to comment on the weather 

225
00:15:06,060 --> 00:15:11,120
Or imitated the sound of a bird to tell a friend that there was a bird nearby 

226
00:15:11,340 --> 00:15:14,180
Then , over hundreds of thousands of years 

227
00:15:14,460 --> 00:15:20,020
Those sounds turned into words that people began to learn as part of their language 

228
00:15:20,030 --> 00:15:25,710
At some point , people started stringing the words together to form sentences 

229
00:15:26,130 --> 00:15:27,810
The other main theory 

230
00:15:27,810 --> 00:15:32,250
Which is more recent , is that people started off by gesture ing 

231
00:15:32,330 --> 00:15:34,270
Pointing at things with their hands

232
00:15:34,270 --> 00:15:37,530
And imitating actions using their bodies 

233
00:15:37,620 --> 00:15:42,220
Eventually , these gestures turned into full sign language 

234
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:46,700
This theory guesses that after developing sign languages 

235
00:15:46,740 --> 00:15:51,300
People eventually started making sounds along with their gestures 

236
00:15:51,430 --> 00:15:56,510
At some point they switched to mostly making sounds that became words

237
00:15:56,510 --> 00:15:58,990
Instead of just using their bodies 

238
00:15:59,190 --> 00:16:01,930
The reason they switched to making sounds 

239
00:16:01,930 --> 00:16:05,060
The theory goes is that talking out loud

240
00:16:05,060 --> 00:16:07,000
Lets you communicate with someone

241
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:08,800
Even when you can't see them 

